folder: Fort Washington Aven & 187th Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
Fort Washington Ave., north from, but not including West 187th Street. On the left, appears Northern Ave., with the Hudson River in the background. Plot shown includes the James Gordon Bennett Estate.
June 1919.
Gift of E. M. Jenks.

folder: Fort Washington Aven & 187th Street (West), Manhattan, NY
text:
Fort Washington Avenue, north from West 187th Street, showing Mrs. Whitherspoon's house and the George Gray Barnard Studio beyond it (view 2). It is the former Sweetser coach house.

View 3 shows the Mission of the Sacred Heart, west side of the avenue, at West 191st Street. The Mother Cabrini High School was later erected here.

E.P. Chrystie               1924
Views 1-3
